cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.GT

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with an extension of a fixed-point logic for expressing properties of probabilistic labeled transition systems.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses an extension of a logic for encoding properties of interest in probabilistic systems, which is relevant to AI.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper deals with a logic for expressing properties of probabilistic systems, which is relevant to programming languages that deal with probabilistic systems.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses a new class of games that generalize standard two-player stochastic games, which could be relevant to data structures and algorithms.
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is also less likely but possible as the paper discusses a game semantics for the extended probabilistic modal mu calculus.
